#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:912
msgid "Mobile Cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:912
msgid ""
"Serve cached pages to smartphones and tablets. When disabled, WordPress "
"dynamically generates every page for mobile visitors."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:913
msgid "Separate Mobile Cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:913
msgid ""
"For themes that output different HTML for desktop and mobile. Maintains "
"separate cache files per device type. Not needed for responsive themes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:914
msgid "Logged-in User Cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:914
msgid ""
"Serve cached pages to logged-in users. SECURITY WARNING: all logged-in users "
"and anonymous visitors share one cached copy of each page, so a page "
"generated for one user — including their admin bar, nonces, or any user-"
"specific content — can be served to other users and to the public. Only "
"enable on sites that serve byte-for-byte identical content to everyone (e.g. "
"membership sites with no per-user output)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:915
msgid "Gzip Compression"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:915
msgid ""
"Pre-compress cache files with gzip. Supported browsers receive the "
"compressed version, reducing transfer size by 60-80%. Recommended for most "
"environments."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:916
msgid "Brotli Compression"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:916
msgid ""
"Enable Brotli compression via mod_brotli (Apache 2.4+). Brotli achieves "
"15-25% better compression than gzip. Requires mod_brotli and .htaccess "
"Optimization to be enabled. Falls back to gzip via mod_deflate if Brotli is "
"unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:917
msgid ".htaccess Optimization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:917
msgid ""
"Write optimization rules to .htaccess. Apache serves cached files directly "
"without invoking PHP, significantly improving response time. Also enables "
"mod_deflate compression and ETag removal. mod_expires and Cache-Control "
"headers are added when \"Enable Browser Cache Headers\" is also on. No "
"effect on Nginx."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:918
msgid "Cache 404 Pages"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:918
msgid ""
"Cache 404 (Not Found) pages. Reduces server load from repeated requests to "
"non-existent URLs. The cached 404 page is served with proper 404 HTTP status "
"code via the PHP drop-in. Note: .htaccess Optimization does not serve cached "
"404 pages (they always go through PHP to ensure the correct status code)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:919
msgid "Mixed HTTP/HTTPS Site"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:919
msgid ""
"Enable only if your site intentionally serves both http:// and https:// "
"versions of the same URL. When disabled (recommended), the cache scheme "
"follows your Site Address setting — safe and tamper-proof. Reverse proxies "
"are auto-detected. When enabled, the drop-in falls back to per-request "
"header detection; sites behind a reverse proxy must also define "
"PRIME_CACHE_TRUST_X_FORWARDED_PROTO in wp-config.php."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:920
msgid "Cache Footprint"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:920
msgid ""
"Append an HTML comment with cache generation time to the source. Useful for "
"verifying cache behavior via \"View Source\". Can be disabled in production."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:925
msgid ".htaccess Active"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:926
msgid ".htaccess Not Writable"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:934
msgid "Enable Varnish Purge"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:934
msgid ""
"Automatically purge the Varnish cache when WordPress content changes. Sends "
"PURGE requests to the configured Varnish server."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:936
msgid "Varnish Server IP"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:938
msgid ""
"One IP address per line. If your Varnish server runs on a different host or "
"port, specify here. Defaults to 127.0.0.1 (localhost)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:945
msgid "Enable Sucuri Purge"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:945
msgid ""
"Automatically clear the Sucuri firewall cache when WordPress content changes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:947
msgid "Sucuri API Key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:949
msgid ""
"Your Sucuri firewall API key. Found in the Sucuri dashboard under API "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:958
msgid "Enable Browser Cache Headers"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:958
msgid ""
"Add Cache-Control and Expires headers to cached responses, both using the "
"lifetimes configured below. HTML Cache-Control is applied by the PHP drop-"
"in. CSS, JS, image, font, and Expires headers require .htaccess Optimization "
"to be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:959
msgid "Immutable Cache-Control"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:959
msgid ""
"Add \"immutable\" directive to Cache-Control for CSS, JS, images, and fonts. "
"Tells the browser the file will never change during its lifetime, preventing "
"conditional revalidation requests (304 checks)."
msgstr ""

