#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1119
msgid "Minify HTML"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1119
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary whitespace from the HTML output to reduce page size. "
"Content inside pre, script, style, and textarea tags is preserved."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1120
msgid "Optimize HTML via DOM Parser"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1120
msgid ""
"Requires \"Minify HTML\" above to be enabled. Switches the minification "
"engine from regex to DOMDocument for deeper optimization — parses the "
"document tree to more aggressively collapse whitespace between block-level "
"elements while preserving inline formatting. Falls back to regex if DOM "
"parsing fails."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1121
msgid "Remove HTML Comments"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1121
msgid ""
"Strip HTML comments from the output. IE conditional comments are preserved."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1122
msgid "Disable WordPress Emoji"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1122
msgid ""
"Remove the emoji inline CSS, wp-emoji-release.min.js script, and DNS "
"prefetch for s.w.org from all pages. Reduces 2 HTTP requests and ~16 KB from "
"every page load. Does not affect actual emoji display in modern browsers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1128
msgid "Minify CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1128
msgid ""
"Remove whitespace, comments, and unnecessary characters from CSS files to "
"reduce file size."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1131
msgid "Combine CSS Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1131
msgid ""
"Merge multiple CSS files into fewer files to reduce HTTP requests. On HTTP/2 "
"servers this may have minimal benefit. Test thoroughly after enabling."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1133
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1201
msgid "Mobile Only"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1133
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1201
msgid ""
"Apply CSS/JS combining only on mobile devices. Desktop uses HTTP/2 "
"multiplexing efficiently without combining. Requires separate mobile cache."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1137
msgid "Excluded CSS Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1139
msgid ""
"One pattern per line. These CSS files will not be minified, combined, or "
"loaded asynchronously. Supports wildcards (*)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1141
msgid "Inline Small CSS Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1141
msgid ""
"Inline CSS files smaller than the threshold directly into the HTML as "
"<style> tags, eliminating HTTP requests for small stylesheets."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1143
msgid "Threshold (bytes)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1148
msgid "Load CSS Asynchronously (Free)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1148
msgid ""
"Convert non-first <link rel=\"stylesheet\"> tags to non-render-blocking "
"loading via media=\"print\" + onload swap. The first stylesheet on the page "
"is intentionally left synchronous to preserve LCP and prevent unstyled flash "
"for above-the-fold content. Use the \"Excluded CSS Files\" list above for "
"additional stylesheets that must remain render-blocking. Pro users get more "
"sophisticated CSS delivery options (Critical CSS, Remove Unused CSS) and "
"should leave this off."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1156
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1157
msgid "Optimize CSS Delivery"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1157
msgid ""
"Improve render performance by optimizing how CSS is loaded. Choose a method "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1161
msgid "Remove Unused CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1165
msgid "Load CSS Asynchronously"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1168
msgid "Auto-Generate Critical CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1168
msgid ""
"Automatically extract above-the-fold Critical CSS for each page to prevent "
"flash of unstyled content (FOUC)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1170
msgid "Fallback Critical CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1172
msgid ""
"Manual critical CSS used as a fallback when auto-generation is not available "
"for a page. Inlined in the <head> to render above-the-fold content "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1175
msgid "Used CSS Safelist"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1177
msgid ""
"CSS selectors or patterns that should never be removed (one per line). Use "
"when Remove Unused CSS incorrectly strips needed styles."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1179
msgid "Async CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1179
msgid ""
"Load all CSS files asynchronously using link[rel=preload] to eliminate "
"render-blocking stylesheets."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1187
msgid "Minify JavaScript"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1187
msgid ""
"Conservative JavaScript size reduction: trims trailing whitespace and "
"collapses blank lines. Comments are preserved (regex-based comment removal "
"is unsafe without a JS parser — gzip handles the bulk of size reduction). "
"Already minified files (.min.js) are skipped."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1188
msgid "Load JavaScript Deferred"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1188
msgid ""
"Add the defer attribute to enqueued scripts (wp_enqueue_script) to eliminate "
"render-blocking JavaScript. Scripts are downloaded in parallel and executed "
"after HTML parsing. Manually inserted scripts in theme templates are not "
"affected on desktop. Note: on mobile, inline jQuery patterns ($"
"(document).ready, $(function(){...})) are automatically wrapped in "
"DOMContentLoaded so they keep working when jQuery itself is deferred."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1189
msgid "Delay JavaScript Execution"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1189
msgid ""
"Delay every external <script src=\"...\"> tag in the HTML output (including "
"third-party / CDN — not limited to wp_enqueue_script handles) until user "
"interaction (scroll, click, keydown, touchstart, mousemove). Inline scripts "
"(no src) are never delayed because they typically set up variables that "
"external scripts depend on (wp_localize_script output, consent_api config, "
"chat widget configs, etc.). Applied on mobile devices only to avoid CLS "
"regression on desktop. Separate mobile cache is automatically enabled when "
"this setting is on. Significantly improves mobile page load metrics but may "
"cause a brief delay on first interaction. Use the exclusion list below for "
"external scripts that must run before interaction."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1192
msgid "Delay Timeout (ms)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1194
msgid ""
"Auto-load delayed scripts after this many milliseconds even without user "
"interaction. 0 = wait for interaction only."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1196
msgid "Delay JS Safe Mode"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1196
msgid ""
"Only delay external (third-party) scripts. All internal scripts from your "
"site (wp-includes, wp-content) load immediately. Reduces performance gains "
"but prevents most compatibility issues."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1199
msgid "Combine JavaScript Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1199
msgid ""
"Merge multiple JS files into fewer files. May break some scripts — test "
"thoroughly. On HTTP/2 the benefit is minimal."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1205
msgid "Excluded JS Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1207
msgid ""
"One pattern per line. These JS files will not be minified or combined. "
"Supports wildcards (*)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1210
msgid "Excluded Inline JavaScript"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1212
msgid ""
"Keywords to identify inline scripts to exclude from optimization. One per "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1215
msgid "Excluded from Defer"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1217
msgid "JS files that should not be deferred. One pattern per line."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1220
msgid "Excluded from Delay"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1222
msgid ""
"JS files that should not be delayed. One pattern per line. Scripts with data-"
"no-delay attribute are always excluded."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1228
msgid "Fonts & Other"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1232
msgid "Combine Google Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1232
msgid ""
"Merge multiple Google Fonts requests into a single request to reduce HTTP "
"round-trips."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1233
msgid "Self-Host Google Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1233
msgid ""
"Download Google Fonts and serve them from your own server. Eliminates "
"external DNS lookups and connections to fonts.googleapis.com and "
"fonts.gstatic.com."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1234
msgid "Host Google Analytics Locally"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1234
msgid ""
"Download and serve the Google Analytics script from your own server. Reduces "
"external requests and improves PageSpeed scores."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1238
msgid "Optimize Google Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1238
msgid ""
"Improves Google Fonts loading: (1) appends display=swap to font URLs so text "
"remains visible during font load (prevents FOIT), (2) loads font CSS "
"asynchronously via media=\"print\"+onload so it does not block rendering, "
"(3) injects a preconnect hint to fonts.gstatic.com to start the connection "
"earlier."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1239
msgid "Remove Query Strings"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1239
msgid ""
"Remove version query strings (?ver=, ?v=) from local CSS and JS file URLs. "
"Improves cacheability by CDNs and proxies that ignore query strings. "
"External URLs are not affected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1245
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1246
msgid "Enable Rewrite for File Optimizer"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1246
msgid ""
"Serve optimized CSS/JS files via clean URLs (/_pc-static/) instead of direct "
"file paths. Uses WordPress rewrite rules for portability. Adds a 1-year "
"Cache-Control max-age for optimal browser caching; the immutable directive "
"is included only when \"Immutable Cache-Control\" is also enabled. "
"Permalinks are flushed automatically when this setting is changed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1251
msgid "Performance Tweaks"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1254
msgid "Use Local jQuery"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1254
msgid ""
"Restore WordPress bundled jQuery when the theme loads it from an external "
"CDN (e.g. cdnjs.cloudflare.com). Eliminates external connection overhead "
"(~600ms on mobile) by serving jQuery from the same origin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1255
msgid "Disable jQuery Migrate"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1255
msgid ""
"Remove jquery-migrate.min.js from the frontend. Most modern jQuery code and "
"plugins no longer need it. Saves ~10 KB per page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1256
msgid "Disable WP Embed"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1256
msgid ""
"Remove wp-embed.min.js and oEmbed discovery links from your pages. Saves ~6 "
"KB of JavaScript per page and makes your content harder to auto-embed via "
"discovery, but the oEmbed REST endpoint still responds — combine with "
"\"Disable oEmbed\" below for full embed prevention."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1257
msgid "Disable Dashicons (Frontend)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1257
msgid ""
"Remove the Dashicons stylesheet for non-logged-in visitors. Saves ~46 KB. "
"Icons remain available for logged-in users and the admin area."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1258
msgid "Remove WordPress Version"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1258
msgid ""
"Remove the WordPress version meta tag and feed generator tag. Minor security "
"improvement — prevents version fingerprinting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1259
msgid "Disable XML-RPC"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1259
msgid ""
"Disable the XML-RPC API via the xmlrpc_enabled filter and remove the X-"
"Pingback header. This does not block access to xmlrpc.php at the server "
"level — use .htaccess or server configuration for full blocking. Not needed "
"if you use the REST API."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1260
msgid "Disable Self-Pingbacks"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1260
msgid ""
"Prevent WordPress from sending pingback requests to your own site when you "
"link to your own posts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1261
msgid "Disable RSS Feeds"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1261
msgid ""
"Disable all RSS/Atom feeds and redirect feed URLs to the homepage. Use only "
"if your site does not need feeds."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1262
msgid "Disable oEmbed"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1262
msgid ""
"Remove oEmbed discovery links, host JavaScript, and REST API route. Prevents "
"remote embedding of your content."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1263
msgid "Disable Gutenberg Block CSS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1263
msgid ""
"Remove wp-block-library, wp-block-library-theme, and WooCommerce block "
"stylesheets. Use only if you are using the Classic Editor and not using any "
"Gutenberg blocks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1264
msgid "Disable Google Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1264
msgid ""
"Dequeue all Google Fonts (fonts.googleapis.com and fonts.bunny.net) loaded "
"by themes and plugins. Use if you self-host fonts or do not need external "
"fonts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1265
msgid "Disable Global Styles (SVG)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1265
msgid ""
"Remove the global-styles inline CSS and SVG filters added by WordPress 6.1+. "
"Saves ~2 KB of inline markup on every page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1266
msgid "Limit DNS Prefetch Hints"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1266
msgid ""
"Limit dns-prefetch and preconnect hints to 4 entries. WordPress auto-adds "
"hints for every external domain, which wastes mobile connections. PageSpeed "
"recommends 4 or fewer."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1274
msgid "Limit Post Revisions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1274
msgid ""
"Limit the maximum number of revisions stored per post. Reduces database "
"bloat over time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1276
msgid "Max Revisions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1278
msgid "0 = disable revisions entirely"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1283
msgid "WooCommerce Script Optimization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1283
msgid ""
"Disable WooCommerce CSS and JavaScript on non-WooCommerce pages (shop, "
"product, archive, cart, checkout, and account pages are excluded). Saves "
"~100 KB+ on regular blog/pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1284
msgid "Disable Cart Fragments AJAX"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1284
msgid ""
"Disable WooCommerce cart fragments AJAX request (wc-"
"ajax=get_refreshed_fragments) on non-cart/checkout pages. This AJAX call "
"runs on every page load and is one of the biggest WooCommerce performance "
"bottlenecks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1289
msgid "WP Head Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1292
msgid "Remove Shortlink"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1292
msgid ""
"Remove the shortlink tag and HTTP header. Not needed if you use pretty "
"permalinks."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1293
msgid "Remove RSD & WLW Manifest"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1293
msgid ""
"Remove Really Simple Discovery and Windows Live Writer manifest links. Only "
"needed for XML-RPC clients."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1294
msgid "Remove REST API Link"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1294
msgid ""
"Remove the REST API discovery link tag and HTTP header from the frontend."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1295
msgid "Disable WordPress Sitemap"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1295
msgid ""
"Disable the built-in WordPress XML sitemap (/wp-sitemap.xml). Use if you "
"have a sitemap plugin like Yoast SEO or Rank Math."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1296
msgid "Add Blank Favicon"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1296
msgid ""
"Add an inline SVG favicon to prevent the browser from requesting a missing "
"favicon.ico (404). Only applied when no site icon is set."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1306
msgid "3rd-Party Script Delay Presets"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1307
msgid ""
"Select known third-party scripts to exclude from JavaScript delay execution. "
"These scripts will load immediately instead of waiting for user interaction."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1418
msgid "Lazy Load Images"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1418
msgid ""
"Add loading=\"lazy\" attribute to images below the fold. The first N images "
"(configurable below) are skipped to preserve above-the-fold LCP performance. "
"Images with fetchpriority=\"high\" are never lazy loaded."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1420
msgid "Skip First N Images"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1422
msgid ""
"Number of leading images per page that bypass lazy loading (typically the "
"LCP candidate and adjacent above-the-fold images). Default 3. Set 0 to lazy-"
"load every image."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1424
msgid "Lazy Load Iframes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1424
msgid ""
"Add loading=\"lazy\" to iframes (YouTube embeds, Google Maps, etc.). "
"Significantly reduces initial page weight for embed-heavy pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1425
msgid "Lazy Load Videos"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1425
msgid ""
"Set preload=\"none\" on video elements to prevent auto-downloading video "
"files until playback is requested."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1426
msgid "Disable WordPress Native Lazy Load"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1426
msgid ""
"Disable the built-in lazy loading added by WordPress 5.5+. Use this if you "
"want Prime Cache to have full control over which images are lazy loaded, or "
"to prevent double lazy-load attributes. When disabled, WordPress will not "
"automatically add loading=\"lazy\" to images and iframes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1428
msgid "Excluded Patterns"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1430
msgid ""
"One pattern per line. Images, iframes, and videos containing these strings "
"will not be lazy loaded."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1436
msgid "Image Optimization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1439
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1441
msgid "YouTube Thumbnail Placeholder"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1439
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1441
msgid ""
"Replace YouTube iframe embeds with a lightweight thumbnail image. The iframe "
"loads only when the user clicks play, saving significant bandwidth and "
"improving page load time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1443
msgid "Add Missing Image Dimensions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1443
msgid ""
"Automatically add width and height attributes to images that are missing "
"them. Prevents Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) — a Core Web Vitals metric. "
"Only works for locally hosted images."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1444
msgid "Strip EXIF Data"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1444
msgid ""
"Remove EXIF metadata (camera model, GPS coordinates, timestamps) from JPEG "
"images on upload. Only JPEG images are processed. Images are re-encoded at "
"quality 92, which may slightly change file size. Improves privacy by "
"stripping location data."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1445
msgid "Resize Oversized Images"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1445
msgid ""
"Automatically resize JPEG and PNG images that exceed the maximum dimensions "
"on upload. WebP, GIF, and AVIF images are not affected. Prevents "
"unnecessarily large images from being stored and served."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1448
msgid "Max Width (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1452
msgid "Max Height (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1467
msgid "Format Conversion (WebP / AVIF)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1472
msgid "Enable Image Conversion"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1473
msgid ""
"Convert JPEG and PNG images to modern formats for smaller file sizes and "
"faster loading."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1480
msgid "WebP"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1481
msgid "Convert images to WebP format. Supported by all modern browsers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1490
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1495
msgid "AVIF"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1491
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1495
msgid ""
"Convert images to AVIF format. Offers superior compression but requires more "
"processing time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1499
msgid ""
"Your server does not support AVIF conversion — AVIF will be skipped even if "
"enabled. (Requires GD with AVIF support or ImageMagick with AVIF.)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1504
msgid "Quality Mode"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1506
msgid "Lossy"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1507
msgid "Lossless"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1508
msgid "Custom"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1512
msgid "WebP Quality"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1516
msgid "AVIF Quality"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1527
msgid "Delivery Method"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1529
msgid "Rewrite (.htaccess)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1530
msgid "<picture> Tag"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1531
msgid "URL Replacement"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1535
msgid "Conversion Engine"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1537
msgid "Auto (Imagick, then GD)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1545
msgid "Target Folders"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1548
msgid "Uploads (wp-content/uploads)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1552
msgid "Themes (wp-content/themes)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1556
msgid "Plugins (wp-content/plugins)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1564
msgid "Auto-Optimize on Upload"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1565
msgid ""
"Automatically convert images when they are uploaded to the media library."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1572
msgid "Delete Larger Conversions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1573
msgid ""
"If the converted file is larger than the original, delete it automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1580
msgid "Exclude PNG Files"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1581
msgid ""
"Skip PNG images during conversion. Useful for PNGs with transparency or "
"sharp graphics where WebP/AVIF offers little benefit. JPEG images are still "
"converted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1591
msgid "Bulk Image Optimization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1592
msgid ""
"Scan and optimize existing images in your media library. Progress is saved — "
"you can pause and resume at any time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1594
msgid "Scan for Unoptimized Images"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1602
msgid "Progress"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1640
msgid "Scanning…"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1641
msgid "No unoptimized images found."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %1$d: number of images processed so far, %2$d: total number of images.
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1642
#, php-format
msgid "Converting %1$d / %2$d…"
msgstr ""

#. translators: %d: number of images processed.
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1643
#, php-format
msgid "Done. Processed %d images."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: error message.
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1644
#, php-format
msgid "Error: %s"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1645
msgid "unknown error"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1646
msgid "network error"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1739
msgid "CDN"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1746
msgid "CDN URL Rewriting"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1747
msgid "Enable CDN"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1747
msgid ""
"Rewrite URLs for static assets (images, CSS, JS) to be served from your CDN "
"hostname. Works with any pull-zone CDN (BunnyCDN, CloudFront, KeyCDN, "
"StackPath, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1748
msgid "Rewrite Relative URLs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1748
msgid ""
"Also rewrite relative URLs (starting with /) in src and href attributes. "
"Disable if your theme uses relative URLs for non-asset links."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1750
msgid "CDN Hostname(s)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1752
msgid ""
"One hostname per line (without https://). Multiple hostnames enable domain "
"sharding — assets are distributed across them in round-robin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1755
msgid "Include Directories"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1757
msgid ""
"Comma-separated directory names. Only URLs containing these paths will be "
"rewritten. Default: wp-content,wp-includes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1760
msgid "Exclude Patterns"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1762
msgid ""
"One pattern per line. URLs containing these strings will not be rewritten to "
"the CDN."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1769
msgid "Cloudflare Cache Sync"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1769
msgid ""
"Automatically purge Cloudflare cache when Prime Cache is cleared. Supports "
"full zone purge and per-URL purge (up to 30 URLs per API call, batched "
"automatically). Small batches are sent immediately; larger batches are "
"deferred to a background task."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1771
msgid "Zone ID"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1773
msgid ""
"Find this in Cloudflare dashboard > your domain > Overview (right sidebar)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1776
msgid "Authentication Method"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1778
msgid "API Token (recommended)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1779
msgid "Global API Key + Email"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1783
msgid "API Token or Global API Key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1786
msgid ""
"API Token: Create a custom token with \"Zone > Cache Purge > Purge\" "
"permission. Global API Key: Use with the email address below. Can also be "
"set via PRIME_CACHE_CF_API_TOKEN constant."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1789
msgid "Cloudflare Account Email"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1791
msgid ""
"Required only when using Global API Key authentication. Not needed for API "
"Token."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1822
msgid "Cache Preloading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1825
msgid "Partial preload:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1825
msgid ""
"Vary Cookies are active. Preloading can only warm the default (no-cookie) "
"variant for each URL. Cookie-specific cache files (e.g. for currency, "
"country, A/B tests) cannot be preloaded and will be generated on the first "
"real visitor request with that cookie value. This is a technical limitation "
"— not a bug."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1828
msgid "Enable Cache Preloading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1830
msgid ""
"Automatically crawl your site to warm the default cache variant (desktop and "
"mobile). Cookie-specific variants cannot be preloaded and are generated on "
"the first real visitor request with that cookie value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1832
msgid ""
"Automatically crawl your site in the background to warm the page cache. "
"Pages are preloaded via non-blocking HTTP requests so visitors always "
"receive cached pages. Preloading restarts after a full cache purge."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1835
msgid "Preload Homepage"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1835
msgid "Include the front page, posts page, and home URL in the preload queue."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1836
msgid "Preload Public Posts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1836
msgid ""
"Preload published posts, pages, and custom post types (most recently "
"modified first)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1837
msgid "Preload Taxonomies"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1837
msgid "Preload category, tag, and custom taxonomy archive pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1841
msgid "Max Posts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1845
msgid "Max Terms"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1849
msgid ""
"Maximum number of posts and taxonomy terms to include in each preload cycle. "
"Higher values warm more pages but take longer to complete."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1852
msgid "Preloader Request Interval (seconds)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1854
msgid ""
"Delay between each preload batch. Each batch sends up to 10 URLs in "
"sequence, then waits this many seconds before the next batch via WP-Cron. "
"Higher values reduce server load but take longer to complete. Preloading "
"automatically pauses when load (weighted 1/5/15-minute average) exceeds 80% "
"of CPU core count or 2.0 — whichever is higher — or when a sudden load spike "
"is detected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1857
msgid "Preload Excluded URLs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1859
msgid ""
"URL path patterns to skip during preloading, one per line. A line matches "
"when it appears anywhere in the URL path; use * as a wildcard for any "
"sequence (for example, /private-area/*)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1865
msgid "Preload Links"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1866
msgid "Enable Link Prefetching"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1866
msgid ""
"Inject a lightweight JavaScript that prefetches internal links when the user "
"hovers over them or when they enter the viewport. The browser downloads the "
"page in advance so the next click feels instant. Rate-limited to 3 links per "
"second. Excluded: admin, login, cart, checkout, and external links."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1873
msgid "Sitemap Preloading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1874
msgid "Enable Sitemap Preloading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1874
msgid ""
"Use your XML sitemap to discover and preload all URLs. More reliable than "
"the default post/taxonomy crawl for sites with custom post types or complex "
"URL structures."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1876
msgid "Sitemap URL"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1878
msgid ""
"Full URL to your XML sitemap. Leave empty to use the WordPress default "
"sitemap."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1884
msgid "Speculation Rules"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1885
msgid "Enable Speculation Rules"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1885
msgid ""
"Use the Speculation Rules API to prerender or prefetch pages. Supported by "
"Chromium-based browsers (Chrome, Edge). Provides near-instant page "
"transitions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1890
msgid "Font Preloading"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1891
msgid "Preload Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1891
msgid ""
"Add preload hints for font files used in above-the-fold content. Reduces "
"font loading delay and prevents flash of invisible text (FOIT)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1896
msgid "LCP Optimization"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1897
msgid "Optimize Largest Contentful Paint"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1897
msgid ""
"Automatically detect and preload the LCP image for each page. Adds "
"fetchpriority=\"high\" and a preload link to accelerate the largest visible "
"element."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1901
msgid "URL patterns to exclude from LCP optimization. One per line."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1907
msgid "Preload Critical Resources"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1909
msgid "Resources to Preload"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1911
msgid ""
"One URL per line. These resources will be preloaded via <link "
"rel=\"preload\"> in the page head. Use for critical fonts, images, or "
"scripts that are discovered late by the browser."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1917
msgid "Prefetch DNS"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1919
msgid "Domains to Prefetch"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1921
msgid ""
"One domain per line (with //). DNS resolution is performed in advance so "
"that external resources load faster when requested."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1927
msgid "Preconnect"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1929
msgid "Origins to Preconnect"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1931
msgid ""
"One origin per line. Establishes early connections (DNS + TCP + TLS) to "
"important third-party origins before the browser needs them."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1949
msgid "Query Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1950
msgid "Ignored Query Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1950
msgid ""
"Comma-separated parameter names. These parameters are stripped and the same "
"cache is served as if they were absent. Register ad-tracking parameters "
"(utm_source, fbclid, gclid, etc.) to prevent unnecessary cache duplication. "
"<strong>Note:</strong> Requests with any query string go through the PHP "
"drop-in (the .htaccess fast-path requires an empty query string), still very "
"fast but not zero-PHP."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1951
msgid "Cached Query Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1951
msgid ""
"Comma-separated parameter names. Each unique value generates a separate "
"cache file. For example, specifying <code>lang</code> creates separate "
"caches for <code>?lang=en</code> and <code>?lang=ja</code>. Use for "
"multilingual plugins or currency switchers. URLs with parameters not in "
"either list are not cached. <strong>Note:</strong> When active, .htaccess "
"fast-path is automatically disabled — all requests are served via the drop-"
"in to ensure correct variant selection (still very fast, but not zero-PHP)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1953
msgid "Cookie-based Cache Splitting"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1954
msgid "Vary Cookie Names"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1954
msgid ""
"Comma-separated cookie names. Different cache files are generated based on "
"each cookie's value, even for the same URL. For example, specifying the "
"<code>currency</code> cookie serves separate caches to users with "
"<code>currency=USD</code> vs <code>currency=JPY</code>. Use for e-commerce "
"currency/country display or A/B testing. <strong>Note:</strong> When "
"active, .htaccess fast-path is automatically disabled — all requests are "
"served via the drop-in to ensure correct variant selection."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1956
msgid "Purge Settings"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1957
msgid "Always Purge URLs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1957
msgid ""
"One URL per line. Whenever any post is published, updated, trashed, or "
"deleted, caches for these URLs are also cleared in addition to the standard "
"related pages (home, categories, tags, author, date archives). Use for "
"sitemaps, custom landing pages, or shortcode-based post listing pages that "
"are not auto-detected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1972
msgid "Allow"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1973
msgid "Reduce Frequency"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1974
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2770
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2785
msgid "Disable"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1977
msgid "Heartbeat"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1983
msgid "Heartbeat API Control"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1988
msgid "Control Heartbeat API"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1989
msgid ""
"The WordPress Heartbeat API sends periodic AJAX requests (wp-admin/admin-"
"ajax.php) to keep sessions alive, auto-save drafts, and show real-time "
"notifications. Reducing or disabling it lowers server load and CPU usage, "
"especially on shared hosting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:1999
msgid "Frontend"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2001
msgid ""
"Heartbeat on public-facing pages. Usually unnecessary — disabling is "
"recommended for most sites."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2009
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2030
msgid "Interval:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2020
msgid "Admin Dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2022
msgid ""
"Heartbeat on wp-admin pages (excluding the post editor). Reducing to 120 "
"seconds is a good balance between functionality and server load."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2041
msgid "Post Editor"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2043
msgid ""
"Heartbeat on the post/page editor. Required for auto-save, post locking, and "
"real-time collaboration. Disabling may cause data loss — \"Allow\" is "
"strongly recommended."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2087
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2095
msgid "Database"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2088
msgid "Database optimization requires Prime Cache Pro."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: number of items cleaned up
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2101
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Database cleanup processed %s items (max 1,000 per task). Run again if more "
"remain."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2112
msgid "Post Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2115
msgid "Revisions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2115
msgid ""
"Delete all post revisions. Revisions are saved every time you update a post "
"and can accumulate over time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2116
msgid "Auto Drafts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2116
msgid ""
"Delete auto-draft posts created automatically by WordPress when you start "
"writing a new post. These are never published."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2117
msgid "Trashed Posts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2117
msgid ""
"Permanently delete posts that are in the trash. These are already removed "
"from the site but still occupy database space."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2134
msgid "Comments Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2137
msgid "Spam Comments"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2137
msgid ""
"Permanently delete all comments marked as spam. These comments have already "
"been filtered out but remain in the database."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2138
msgid "Trashed Comments"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2138
msgid "Permanently delete comments that are in the trash."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2155
msgid "Transients Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2158
msgid "Expired Transients"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2158
msgid ""
"Delete only expired transients. These are temporary options that have passed "
"their timeout and are no longer needed. Safe to clean."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2159
msgid "All Transients"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2159
msgid ""
"Delete all transients, including active ones. Transients are recreated as "
"needed by plugins and WordPress core. Use with caution — may briefly slow "
"down the site while they regenerate."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2176
msgid "Database Tables"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2181
msgid "Optimize Tables"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2182
msgid ""
"Run OPTIMIZE TABLE on non-InnoDB WordPress tables with fragmented space. "
"InnoDB tables are excluded because they handle fragmentation internally and "
"OPTIMIZE can cause heavy table rebuilds on large tables."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2189
msgid "Automatic Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2194
msgid "Schedule Automatic Cleanup"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2195
msgid ""
"Automatically run all enabled cleanup tasks above on a schedule via WP-Cron. "
"Only the options toggled on above will be cleaned."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2199
msgid "Cleanup Frequency"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2201
msgid "Daily"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2202
msgid "Weekly"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2203
msgid "Monthly"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2212
msgid "Please back up your database before running cleanup."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2213
msgid ""
"Database cleanup operations permanently delete data such as revisions, "
"drafts, and comments. These actions cannot be undone. We strongly recommend "
"creating a full database backup using your hosting control panel or a backup "
"plugin before proceeding."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2220
msgid ""
"Run database cleanup now? Up to 1,000 items will be processed per run. This "
"cannot be undone."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2221
msgid "Run Cleanup Now"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2245
msgid "Post Publish / Update"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2245
msgid ""
"Clear related caches when a post, page, or custom post type is published or "
"updated. Purges the post URL, home page, posts page, author archive, term "
"archives, date archives, and CPT archive — first page only. Pagination (/"
"page/2/, etc.) is left for natural expiry to preserve cache hit rate."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2246
msgid "Post Trash / Delete"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2246
msgid ""
"Clear related caches when a post is moved to trash or permanently deleted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2247
msgid "Comment Changes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2247
msgid ""
"Clear the post page, home page, and posts page cache when a comment is "
"posted, approved, edited, trashed, or deleted. (Home/posts page cleared "
"because they typically display comment counts and recent-comments widgets.)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2248
msgid "Term Changes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2248
msgid ""
"Clear the term archive (including pagination), home page, and posts page "
"when a category, tag, or custom taxonomy term is created, edited, or deleted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2249
msgid "Theme Switch"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2249
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when the active theme is changed. Theme changes "
"typically affect all pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2250
msgid "Permalink Change"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2250
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when the permalink structure is updated. All cached "
"URLs become invalid."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2251
msgid "Plugin Activate / Deactivate"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2251
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when any plugin is activated or deactivated. Plugin "
"changes may alter page output, menus, or widgets."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2252
msgid "Customizer Save"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2252
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when theme customizer settings are saved. Changes to "
"site identity, colors, layouts, and header/footer affect all pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2253
msgid "Widget Update"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2253
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when widgets are added, removed, or rearranged. "
"Widgets appear on multiple pages via sidebars and footers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2254
msgid "Navigation Menu Update"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2254
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache when a navigation menu is created, edited, or "
"deleted. Menus are typically displayed on every page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2255
msgid "WordPress Core Update"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2255
msgid ""
"Clear the entire cache after WordPress core is updated. Core updates may "
"change HTML output, scripts, and styles."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2256
msgid "User Profile Update"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2256
msgid ""
"Clear the author archive (including pagination), home page, and posts page "
"when a user profile is updated or a user is deleted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2260
msgid ""
"Choose which WordPress events automatically clear the cache. Disabling a "
"trigger means that event will no longer purge cached pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2267
msgid "Purge Triggers"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2286
msgid ""
"Note: When .htaccess Optimization is enabled, only simple patterns are used "
"in the .htaccess fast-path."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2288
msgid "URL patterns to never cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2288
msgid ""
"Enter URL path patterns separated by <code>|</code>. Use <code>*</code> as a "
"wildcard. Matched URLs are always dynamically generated by WordPress. "
"Specify WooCommerce cart/checkout, my-account pages, or any page with user-"
"specific content."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2289
msgid "Cookies that disable caching"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2289
msgid ""
"Enter cookie name patterns separated by <code>|</code>. Use <code>*</code> "
"as a wildcard. When any listed cookie is present, the request is not cached. "
"WordPress login cookies are excluded automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2290
msgid "User agents to never cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2290
msgid ""
"Enter user-agent patterns separated by <code>|</code>. Use <code>*</code> as "
"a wildcard. Matched browsers or crawlers receive uncached responses."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2291
msgid "Referrers to never cache"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2291
msgid ""
"Enter referrer URL patterns separated by <code>|</code>. Use <code>*</code> "
"as a wildcard. Requests from matching referrers are excluded from the cache."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2298
msgid "Wildcard"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2316
msgid "Settings imported successfully."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2318
msgid "Settings imported with warnings."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2332
msgid "Import failed. Please upload a valid Prime Cache settings JSON file."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: preset name (e.g. "Standard", "Aggressive")
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2339
#, php-format
msgid "\"%s\" preset applied successfully."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: preset name supplied by the user
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2345
#, php-format
msgid "Unknown preset \"%s\". No changes were made."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2351
msgid "Optimization Presets"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2352
msgid ""
"Quickly apply a preset configuration based on your comfort level. You can "
"customize individual settings afterward."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2363
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2376
msgid "Auto"
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2364
msgid ""
"Recommended — analyzes your environment and applies optimal settings "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: preset name
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2376
#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:2412
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Apply the \"%s\" preset? Settings included in the preset will overwrite your "
"current values; settings the preset does not touch (rejected URIs, "
